  "texts": [
    "In the immediate present (i.e., Gaby is in front of the door), Paula also directs the interviewer's attention to the door, as she utters, 'oh, Gaby is here'.",
    "Deriving from the text message, that Gaby is waiting in front of the door, actual happenings in Paula's immediated environment made her move and enact a weaker sense of human presencing. foot_7 Fig.",
    "7 Paula in the physical classroom with the other group members Gaby made herself present by sending a text message to Paula's phone and by standing on the other side of the door.",
    "However, she remains invisible to Paula (i.e., not directly perceivable).",
    "With gaze and gesture aligned, Paula extends her orientation space by pointing to the door and shifting attention to Gaby, who is 'present.'"
